&lt;h2 id=&#34;devon-united-mine-and-shaft&#34;&gt;Devon United Mine and Shaft
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/p/smeardon-down/14.jpg&#34;
	width=&#34;1000&#34;
	height=&#34;750&#34;
	srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/p/smeardon-down/14_hu_c7d641bd4852bcf9.jpg 480w, http://localhost:1313/p/smeardon-down/14_hu_84c4c1244c780d95.jpg 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;A shaft of Devon United Mine which had north, central and south sections&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;133&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;320px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The North mine was worked for copper until the 1850&amp;rsquo;s. The central and South mines were worked for tin and arsenic until 1922.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The South mine site went down to 50 fathoms (300 feet) and produced most of the tin. The central section produced mainly arsenic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://www.mindat.org/loc-235493.html&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Mindat page for Devon United Mines&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/p/smeardon-down/15.jpg&#34;
	width=&#34;1000&#34;
	height=&#34;750&#34;
	srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/p/smeardon-down/15_hu_8aca561208e32a16.jpg 480w, http://localhost:1313/p/smeardon-down/15_hu_5d12298dee813362.jpg 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;Ruined mine buildings&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;133&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;320px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
